    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-03T09:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-03T09:50:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">293.1111/6–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 206<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation at the Geneva
                            Conference</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d206fn1">A note on the source text states that the telegram
                        was sent at <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>’ direction; it was
                        drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MDII1">MacArthur</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-03T10:50:00-04:00"
                            >June 3, 1954—10:50 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 152. From Secretary. Re Secto 350.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d206fn2">
                        <ref target="#d203">Document 203</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I concur in your recommendation that a member of <gloss target="#t_USDel1"
                            >USDel</gloss> Geneva accompany <persName corresp="#p_TH1"
                            >Trevelyan</persName> in at least one meeting with Chinese Communists re
                        release Americans now in Chinese hands.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>There are disadvantages in having <persName corresp="#p_RWS1"
                            >Robertson</persName>, who is an Asst Secretary, represent U.S. in such
                        a meeting. However, your point re level of representation is well taken and
                        therefore I authorize <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Alexis Johnson</persName>
                        (who is accredited to a Communist country and has had experience in
                        negotiations with Chinese re Korea) to accompany <persName corresp="#p_TH1"
                            >Trevelyan</persName>.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Please keep us informed re date meeting will occur.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
